Figure 4: Question 2: Diagram
Problem statement
The electromagnet shown in Fig. P1.8 can be used to lift a length of steel strip. The coil has 500
turns and can carry a current of 20 amps without overheating. The magnetic material has negligible
reluctance at ux densities up to 1.4 tesla. Determine the maximum air gap for which a ux density
of 1.4 tesla can be established with a coil current of 20 amps. Neglect magnetic leakage and fringing
of ux at the air gap.
The question is from Sen 3rd edition, I could use a citation, but I know what I mean.
